    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-30T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-30T09:00:00-05:00" n="394"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d394">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/913: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-30T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >October 30, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 30—11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>165. I was informed today by the Director General of the Foreign Office that the
                    King will reenter Athens on the 17th of November and that diplomats
                    “unfortunately” could not be invited to attend the ceremonies in advance of
                    recognition but that Greek Legations abroad would soon request foreign
                    governments to provide their representatives with new letters of credence.</p>
                <p>The above indicates that the approaching plebiscite is expected only to legalize
                    decisions already taken. All leading Republicans are under surveillance and
                    Papanastasiou and Papandreou have been ordered deported to the Islands. Martial
                    law has been raised but a strong decree provides for sanctions against the press
                    or individuals for words or actions tending to disturb the existing regime.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacVeagh</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
